  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n---\n## 2026-03-31 09:38 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 1/Meta] MEMORY.md Major Update \u2014 Persisting Overnight Research\n\n**Task:** Update MEMORY.md with all findings from tonight's 10-rotation research session. Memory was stale (last updated Mar 30 22:08).\n\n**Changes made:**\n1. **V5 Roadmap section rewritten** \u2014 old \"Queued Strategy Changes\" replaced with structured V5a/V5b/V5c/consolidation plan with dates, specs, and per-indicator performance table\n2. **Copy Intelligence section updated** \u2014 marked as DEAD for 5-min markets with explanation\n3. **Infrastructure section updated** \u2014 added liquidation detector, HL closer script, marked old copy pipeline for removal\n4. **Key Mar 31 research findings** \u2014 new section with tonight's 9 major discoveries\n5. **Indicator logging bug** \u2014 updated status (likely fixed, waiting for 11h trade confirmation)\n6. **V5 OBI weighting** \u2014 re-validated (was incorrectly \"invalidated\" due to pre-fix timing bug)\n7. **HL recapitalization** \u2014 reversed to consolidation (HL\u2192PM, not PM\u2192HL)\n\n**Why this matters:** MEMORY.md is persistent across sessions. Without this update, the next session would still believe:\n- Copy trading works (it doesn't)\n- OBI weighting is invalidated (it's our best indicator)\n- HL should receive more capital (it should lose capital to PM)\n- V5 is a vague list of ideas (it's now a concrete 3-phase plan with patches)\n\n**Next:** 11h trading window in 82 minutes. Regime is RANGE (1/6). Bot will trade. First trade confirms indicator logging fix.\n\n---\n## 2026-03-31 09:08 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 4] Liq Detector Calibration: 5h Data Analysis + ETH Contagion Fix\n\n**Task:** Analyze 5 hours of liquidation detector data to calibrate thresholds and discover signal patterns.\n\n**Dataset:** 59 snapshots (04:13-09:08 UTC), BTC $66,743-$67,722\n\n**Finding 1 \u2014 BTC OI thresholds are correctly calibrated:**\n- OI std dev: 0.23%/5min\n- P10: -0.34% | P90: +0.27%\n- Current liq threshold (0.5% OI drop) catches ~5% of windows \u2192 appropriate sensitivity\n- Not too noisy (would obscure real events), not too quiet (catches cascades)\n\n**Finding 2 \u2014 Raw OI direction does NOT predict BTC price (54%):**\n- OI changes alone are noise for 5-min price prediction on BTC\n- BTC is too liquid \u2014 small OI changes are normal market breathing\n- This means our liq detector should only signal on EXTREME events, not gradual OI drift \u2705\n\n**Finding 3 \u2014 OI SPIKE \u2192 price DROP (71%, n=7, preliminary):**\n- When BTC OI rises sharply (>0.2%), price tends to drop next 5 minutes\n- Theory: new longs at extended prices \u2192 immediate overextension pullback\n- Too small sample to act on, but worth tracking for V5c\n\n**Finding 4 \u2014 ETH CASCADE causes BTC contagion (confirmed):**\n- Regular ETH liq (04:30): BTC moved -0.02% \u2192 no impact\n- ETH CASCADE (07:15): BTC dropped **-0.22% in 5min, -0.24% in 10min**\n- Cross-asset contagion is REAL for CASCADE events\n- **FIX DEPLOYED:** Updated `liquidation-detector.py` to set pm_a",
